# Owlet Baby Care
**Category:** ventures
**Domain:** infant health monitoring / baby tech
**Website:** owletcare.com

## Overview
Owlet Baby Care designs and sells wearable baby monitors that track an infant’s heart rate and oxygen saturation in real time. The core product is the Owlet Smart Sock, a soft bootie worn on a baby’s foot that sends data to a base station and a companion smartphone app. Alerts are triggered if readings fall outside preset ranges, aiming to give parents early warning of potential respiratory or cardiac issues.

Founded in 2012, Owlet gained attention for its focus on reducing the risk of Sudden Infant Death Syndrome (SIDS) through continuous monitoring. The company later expanded into smart cameras and other connected nursery devices. As of 2024, Owlet has shipped millions of Smart Socks worldwide and has raised significant venture capital, though it has also faced regulatory scrutiny from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) over whether its devices require medical clearance.

## Utah connection
Owlet was founded and is headquartered in Lehi, Utah, placing it at the heart of the state’s Silicon Slopes tech ecosystem. The company benefits from Utah’s skilled engineering and healthcare talent pool, and its growth has helped establish the region as a hub for digital health and wearable technology startups.

